    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1362"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/587a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1913</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>See Department’s October 10. The Department is advised that the contract with the
                    bankers was signed October 8, so that the Nicaraguan Government had no
                    opportunity to cause insertion of the clause recommended by the Department.</p>
                <p>It is, however, gratifying to the Department to learn from the bankers that by
                    agreement with Señor Cuadra $400,000 has been set apart and will not be drawn
                    against by Nicaragua pending arrangement with the Department of the Claims
                    Commission matter.</p>
                <p>Communicate the substance of this telegram to the Government of Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
